{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require all police conduct complaints & appeals to be referred to the IOPC",
        "additional_details": "This would help to ensure that there is no perception of bias in how such complaints and appeals are handled.",
        "background": "The Government should amend the Police Reform Act 2002 to remove individual police forces\u2019 right to investigate complaints and appeals against its own officers\u2019 conduct. Such complaints and appeals should always be referred to the Independent Office for Police Conduct (IOPC).",
